A queue of cars, trucks, buses and taxis stretches for kilometres. Courtesy #DStv403 BEITBRIDGE BORDER POST - The Chairperson of the Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs, Bongani Bongo, is calling for urgent intervention at the Beitbridge border post with Zimbabwe. Bongo says government needs to act fast to come up with strategies to deal with the congestion but authorities say it will take weeks to clear the massive backlog of traffic. A queue of cars, trucks, buses and taxis stretches for kilometres. READ: Beitbridge border chaos caused by truck drivers: Motsoaledi eNCA saw at least two people die while waiting to cross the border. Some travellers say they've been stuck for a week now. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge shares more details in the video above.